和新冠病毒同名的科罗娜啤酒，突然成了啤酒行业的大赢家。
Corona, which bears the same name as the new crown virus, suddenly became a big winner in the beer industry.
嘤肉卫星。
Twist satellites.
趣闻。
Interesting news.
塞翁失马。
He lost his horse.
。
.
科罗娜啤酒，英文名称为“Corona”，这个享誉世界的啤酒品牌很不巧，刚好和最近肆虐的新型冠状病毒共享了一个英文名字。
Corona, the world-renowned beer brand that happens to share an English name with the new coronavirus that recently raged on it, is unlucky.
。
.
由于在英语里，冠状病毒的名称为“Coronavirus”（Corona一词在拉丁语中有皇冠之意），因此在疫情爆发的初期，不明真相的外国网友在搜索栏输入病毒名称时，随着新闻跳出来的往往还有躺着中枪的科罗娜啤酒。
Since the coronavirus is known in English as Coronavirus (Corona is the Latin word for coronavirus), in the early days of the outbreak, unknown foreign netizens typed the name of the virus into the search box, often followed by Corona, who was shot in the back.
。
.
根据Google Trends显示，在今年1月18日至26日，关于“Corona beer virus”（科罗娜啤酒病毒）的搜索量增加了近2300%；而“Beer coronavirus”（啤酒冠状病毒）的搜索量同样激增了3233%。
According to Google Trends, searches for the Corona Beer virus increased by nearly 2,300 percent from January 18 to 26, while those for Beer coronavirus also surged by 3,233 percent.
。
.
至少在看得见的社交网络上，仍有部分人会认为科罗娜啤酒和流感病毒有一定的关联性。
At least on visible social networks, some people still think Corona has something to do with the flu virus.
上个月，国外的推特上甚至还有一则人们将科罗娜啤酒倒入水槽，并声称自己是在“消灭病毒”的视频被网友频繁转发。
Last month, foreign tweets even featured a video of people pouring Corona beer into a sink and claiming they were "killing the virus," which netizens frequently relayed.
。
.
虽然这只是个案，大部分人心里还是分得清啤酒和病毒的区别，但现实里，多数人总是会下意识排斥给自己带来恐惧的名字，和一个危险的病毒同名，终归不是什么好事。
Although this is a case in point, most people are aware of the difference between beer and virus, but in reality, most people subconsciously reject the name that brings fear to themselves. It's not a good thing to have the same name as a dangerous virus.
。
.
正因为如此，前段时间国外有不少媒体甚至是统计机构都宣称因为疫情的影响，“科罗娜啤酒”这一品牌将遭到一定程度的影响。
As a result, a number of foreign media and even statistical agencies have claimed that the impact of the epidemic, the "Corona Beer" brand will be affected to some extent.
纽约一家名为5W的公关公司曾给出了相应的调查数据：在冠状病毒的影响下，有38%的美国人表示不会在继续购买科罗娜啤酒。
Coronavirus corona: 38 percent of Americans would not buy Corona at all, according to figures from a New York-based public relations firm called 5W.
。
.
人们更愿意相信一款与负面事物同名的产品，在特殊时期确实会遭到部分人的抵触。
People are more likely to believe that a product with the same name as a negative thing does meet with resistance from some in a particular period of time.
但最近，科罗娜官方终于站出来澄清了这则谣言，据相关负责人表示，在疫情持续的这段期间，科罗娜始终保持不错的销售成绩，“没有看到这对我们的员工、设施或者运营造成任何影响，我们的业务仍旧保持良好的势头。
But recently, Corona officials came forward to clear up the rumor, saying that during the period of the epidemic, Corona had maintained good sales results, "not seeing any impact on our staff, facilities or operations.
”。
"
根据外媒Wired的解释，频繁的听到“Corona”一词，无论它是否和病毒相关，始终会强化人们的记忆。
According to the foreign media Wired, the word "Corona" is frequently heard, whether or not it is associated with a virus, and it always reinforces memories.
“当你想买啤酒，或者走进一间酒吧时，人们依旧会点科罗娜啤酒，和病毒带来的恐慌无关，只是因为这仅仅是人们第一时间会想到的啤酒品牌。
"When you want to buy a beer or walk into a bar, people still order Corona, which has nothing to do with the virus, just because it's just the beer brand people first think of.
”。
"
之前5W公司给出调查数据也遭到了人们的质疑，据《大西洋月刊》调查后给出的报道，这家公司的统计样本仅有700人，且皆为本身有饮酒习惯的对象，而提出的调查问题也极具诱导性，仅统计“人们是否愿意购买科罗娜啤酒”，而并未要求说明这一举动背后的原因，大部分受访者很可能本身就不喜欢这一品牌。
The poll, conducted by Atlantic Monthly magazine and based on a sample of only 700 people, asked a very instructive question about whether people would be willing to buy Corona, without asking why, and most probably didn't like the brand themselves.
。
.
但为什么之前人们更愿意相信或传播有关“冠状病毒导致啤酒的销量下降”的新闻？。
But why were people more likely to believe or spread news about the "coronavirus causing the decline in beer sales"?
“因为多数美国人更愿意相信自己的同胞是愚蠢的，而这个谣言刚好证实了他们内心的偏见。
"Because most Americans are more likely to believe that their compatriots are stupid, and the rumor only confirms their inner bias.
”《大西洋月刊》最后总结道。
"concluded the Atlantic Monthly Bulletin.
。
.
